sentences.content: My name is Ronlyn Goo.
I live in Saratoga, California.
I have been recovering from a hemorrhagic stroke since in 2015.
I was born in San Francisco.
I grew up in Pacifica, a few miles south of San Francisco along the coast.
My dad and mom raised me and my two younger sisters, Jaylynne and Stacy.
I studied Chemical Engineering at UC Berkeley.
I met my best friend forever Aruna freshman year.
I also met my future husband Wen Eng as junior.
He was in the same major as me.
We started dating right away...
but for a long time after.
After working a few years, I went to Stanford GSB for an MBA.
I wanted to finish my education before getting married.
We got married in Pacifica at my childhood parish.
We held our reception in San Franscisco.
The ferry building is in the background.
We been married to my spouse for over 30 years.
We have two children, David and Robert.
David is 28 years old.
He graduated from Stanford and cofounded his own company in 2019.
Robert is 26 years old.
He graduated from Caltech and also cofounded his own company recently.
I was a CEO presenting to my board when I had my stroke.
I had a severe hemorrhagic stroke when I was 52 years old.
I was initially in a coma for a week including two stroke codes.
I woke with right side impairment and severe aphasia.
I could only speak one word: after.
Then "afternoon."
I spent two months in hospitals.

heading.content: What is my occupation since then

sentences.content: I was in a wheelchair for the next year.
I had to learn to walk again.
I relearned to walk inside an exo-skeleton robot.
Two neuro physical therapists helped me to keep my balance.
I was proud to give away my wheelchair after a year.
I used a exp-skeleton robot to help relearn to walk.
I have also attended ATP at Cal State East Bay in Hayward, California.
I have attended Aphasia Recovery Connection and Lingraphica.
I have attended speech therapy at Brooklyn College in New York.
I have attended Speech Recovery Pathways in Southern California virtually.
I attended Voices of Hope for Aphasia in St. Petersburg, Florida virtually.
I have attended Nova Southeastern in Fort Lauderdale, Florida virtually.
I have attended The Aphasia Network in Portland, Oregon virtually.
I have attended Buzzworthy from The Aphasia Network virtually.
I have worked with Paul Posillo from Rhode Island virtually.
I have attended Thursday Education and Training based in Boston, Massachusetts.
I walk around the park near my home.
I walk up to ten laps in an hour.
I ride my recumbent tricycle.
I read (by listening to) books using audible.
Where the Crawdads Sing
The Nightingale
Water for Elephants
A Man Called Ove
The Hunting Party
Becoming.
I enjoy painting in watercolors and acrylics.
I started with plants and flowers.
I bake desserts.
I am gardening.
I like growing plants from seedllngs.
My favorite vegetables and fruit to grow are tomatoes, strawberries and eggplants.
I like the Golden State Warriors, especially Steph Curry.
They are champions.
Since my stroke, I travelled to Hawaii and up and down the west coast.
I have been to Seattle, Portland, Eugene, San Francisco, Santa Barbara, Los Angeles, and San Diego.
I am trying my hardest to get better!!!
